\title{Pytorch Lightning}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Deep learning framework (PyTorch Lightning). Organize PyTorch code into LightningModules, configure Trainers for multi-GPU/TPU, implement data pipelines, callbacks, logging (W&B, TensorBoard), distributed training (DDP, FSDP, DeepSpeed), for scalable neural network training."}

\subtree{
\title{PyTorch Lightning}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{PyTorch Lightning is a deep learning framework that organizes PyTorch code to eliminate boilerplate while maintaining full flexibility. Automate training workflows, multi-device orchestration, and implement best practices for neural network training and scaling across multiple GPUs/TPUs.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{Building, training, or deploying neural networks using PyTorch Lightning}
\li{Organizing PyTorch code into LightningModules}
\li{Configuring Trainers for multi-GPU/TPU training}
\li{Implementing data pipelines with LightningDataModules}
\li{Working with callbacks, logging, and distributed training strategies (DDP, FSDP, DeepSpeed)}
\li{Structuring deep learning projects professionally}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. LightningModule - Model Definition}
\p{Organize PyTorch models into six logical sections:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Initialization} - \code{\startverb \strong{init}()\stopverb} and \code{\startverb setup()\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Training Loop} - \code{\startverb training_step(batch, batch_idx)\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Validation Loop} - \code{\startverb validation_step(batch, batch_idx)\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Test Loop} - \code{\startverb test_step(batch, batch_idx)\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Prediction} - \code{\startverb predict_step(batch, batch_idx)\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Optimizer Configuration} - \code{\startverb configure_optimizers()\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Quick template reference:} See \code{\startverb scripts/template_lightning_module.py\stopverb} for a complete boilerplate.}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/lightning_module.md\stopverb} for comprehensive method documentation, hooks, properties, and best practices.}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Trainer - Training Automation}
\p{The Trainer automates the training loop, device management, gradient operations, and callbacks. Key features:}

\ul{
\li{Multi-GPU/TPU support with strategy selection (DDP, FSDP, DeepSpeed)}
\li{Automatic mixed precision training}
\li{Gradient accumulation and clipping}
\li{Checkpointing and early stopping}
\li{Progress bars and logging}
}

\p{\strong{Quick setup reference:} See \code{\startverb scripts/quick_trainer_setup.py\stopverb} for common Trainer configurations.}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/trainer.md\stopverb} for all parameters, methods, and configuration options.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. LightningDataModule - Data Pipeline Organization}
\p{Encapsulate all data processing steps in a reusable class:}

\ol{
\li{\code{\startverb prepare_data()\stopverb} - Download and process data (single-process)}
\li{\code{\startverb setup()\stopverb} - Create datasets and apply transforms (per-GPU)}
\li{\code{\startverb train_dataloader()\stopverb} - Return training DataLoader}
\li{\code{\startverb val_dataloader()\stopverb} - Return validation DataLoader}
\li{\code{\startverb test_dataloader()\stopverb} - Return test DataLoader}
}

\p{\strong{Quick template reference:} See \code{\startverb scripts/template_datamodule.py\stopverb} for a complete boilerplate.}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/data_module.md\stopverb} for method details and usage patterns.}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Callbacks - Extensible Training Logic}
\p{Add custom functionality at specific training hooks without modifying your LightningModule. Built-in callbacks include:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{ModelCheckpoint} - Save best/latest models}
\li{\strong{EarlyStopping} - Stop when metrics plateau}
\li{\strong{LearningRateMonitor} - Track LR scheduler changes}
\li{\strong{BatchSizeFinder} - Auto-determine optimal batch size}
}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/callbacks.md\stopverb} for built-in callbacks and custom callback creation.}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Logging - Experiment Tracking}
\p{Integrate with multiple logging platforms:}

\ul{
\li{TensorBoard (default)}
\li{Weights & Biases (WandbLogger)}
\li{MLflow (MLFlowLogger)}
\li{Neptune (NeptuneLogger)}
\li{Comet (CometLogger)}
\li{CSV (CSVLogger)}
}

\p{Log metrics using \code{\startverb self.log("metric_name", value)\stopverb} in any LightningModule method.}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/logging.md\stopverb} for logger setup and configuration.}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Distributed Training - Scale to Multiple Devices}
\p{Choose the right strategy based on model size:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{DDP} - For models <500M parameters (ResNet, smaller transformers)}
\li{\strong{FSDP} - For models 500M+ parameters (large transformers, recommended for Lightning users)}
\li{\strong{DeepSpeed} - For cutting-edge features and fine-grained control}
}

\p{Configure with: \code{\startverb Trainer(strategy="ddp", accelerator="gpu", devices=4)\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/distributed_training.md\stopverb} for strategy comparison and configuration.}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Best Practices}
\ul{
\li{Device agnostic code - Use \code{\startverb self.device\stopverb} instead of \code{\startverb .cuda()\stopverb}}
\li{Hyperparameter saving - Use \code{\startverb self.save_hyperparameters()\stopverb} in \code{\startverb \strong{init}()\stopverb}}
\li{Metric logging - Use \code{\startverb self.log()\stopverb} for automatic aggregation across devices}
\li{Reproducibility - Use \code{\startverb seed_everything()\stopverb} and \code{\startverb Trainer(deterministic=True)\stopverb}}
\li{Debugging - Use \code{\startverb Trainer(fast_dev_run=True)\stopverb} to test with 1 batch}
}

\p{\strong{Detailed documentation:} Read \code{\startverb references/best_practices.md\stopverb} for common patterns and pitfalls.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Workflow}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Define model:}}
}

\p{def training_step(self, batch, batch_idx): x, y = batch loss = F.cross_entropy(self.model(x), y) self.log("train_loss", loss) return loss}

\p{def configure_optimizers(self): return torch.optim.Adam(self.parameters())}

\pre{\startverb

2. **Prepare data:**
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Option 1: Direct DataLoaders}
\p{train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=32)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Option 2: LightningDataModule (recommended for reusability)}
\p{dm = MyDataModule(batch_size=32)}

\pre{\startverb

3. **Train:**
\stopverb}

\p{trainer = L.Trainer(max_epochs=10, accelerator="gpu", devices=2) trainer.fit(model, train_loader)  # or trainer.fit(model, datamodule=dm)}

\pre{\startverb

\stopverb}
}
}

